>> source: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/spring-tabbouleh
>> time required: 45 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/spring-tabbouleh-019158d.jpg?resize=768,574

Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/ gas 6. Mix 4 tbsp @oil{6%tbsp} with the @garam masala{1%tbsp} and some seasoning. Toss with the @chickpeas{201%g} in a large roasting tin, then cook for ~{15%min}s until starting to crisp. Tip in the @mixed{250%g} grains, @peas{250%g} and lemon zest. Mix well, then return to the oven for about ~{10%min}s until warmed through.

Transfer to a large bowl or platter, then toss through the herbs, @radishes{250%g}, @cucumber{1}, remaining oil and lemon juice. Season to taste and scatter over the @pomegranate seeds{}. Any leftovers will be good for lunch the next day.
